[[Translation:en/Manual/Console Commands]]
Default Commands

''(comands marked with r1620 will be aviable in version 0.3.6)''
----
* '''alias <name> <command>''' -- ''Create an alias''
** This command creates an alias named <name>, which executes the commands specified in <command>. To read more about aliases, look at [[en/Manual/Console Aliases|Aliases]]
* '''ban <Client-ID> <warning>(r1620)</warning>''' -- ''ban client''
* '''banlist <warning>(r1620)</warning>''' -- ''list banned clients''
* '''clients''' -- ''Show information about the currently connected network clients''
* '''connect <server>''' -- ''Connect to the network game running at <server>''
* '''debug_level <level>''' -- ''Set the debug level to <level> (0-9, the higher the more sensitive)''
* '''dump_vars''' -- ''Print out all known variables and their values''
* '''echo <text>''' -- ''Print out <text>''
* '''echoc <color> <text>''' -- ''Prints out <text> in color <color>''
* '''exec <file>''' -- ''Execute the script file located at <file>''
* '''exit''' -- ''Quit the game''
* '''goto_dir <dir-no> <warning>(r1620)</warning>''' -- ''Change directory. Use list_files in advance.''
* '''help''' -- ''Display simple console help''
* '''info_cmd <command>''' -- ''Show technical information on the command <command>''
* '''info_var <variable>''' -- ''Show technical information on the variable <variable>''
* '''kick <player>''' -- ''Kick the player with player-id <player> from the network game''
* '''list_aliases''' -- ''List all available aliases''
* '''list_cmds <filter>''' -- ''List all available commands''
* '''list_files <warning>(r1620)</warning>''' -- ''List files of current directory. Use goto_dir to change the working directory.''
* '''list_vars <filter>''' -- ''List all available variables''
* '''load <file-no> <warning>(r1620)</warning>''' -- ''Load saved game by the given file number. Use list_files in advance.''
* '''name "<client's new name>"''' -- ''changes existing client's name to a new name specified''
* '''newgame''' -- ''Start a new game''
* '''printf <format> [<arg_1> .. <arg_n>]''' -- ''Print out a string, printf style''
* '''printfc <color> <format> [<arg_1> .. <arg_n>]''' -- ''Print out a string with color <color>, printf style''
* '''quit''' -- ''Quit the game''
* '''random''' -- ''Generate a random number''
* '''rcon <password> <comand> <warning>(r1620)</warning>''' -- ''Execute a remote control comand on the server while connected as a client. Password must be set by "set rcon_pw <password>" in advance.''
* '''reset_company <company-id>''' -- ''a company is deleted by a server using this command''
* '''return''' -- ''Return (exit) from the running script''
* '''say <text>''' -- ''Send a chatmessage containing <text> to all players''
* '''say_client <client> <text>''' -- ''Send a chatmessage containing <text> to the client with client-id <client>''
* '''say_player <player> <text>''' -- ''Send a chatmessage containing <text> to the player with player-id <player>''
* '''scan_files <file-name> <warning>(r1620)</warning>''' -- ''Result is position of the given file. See list_files.''
* '''screenshot [big/no_con]''' -- ''Make a screenshot''
** By default the screenshot will be made of your screen. If you supply the optional [big] paramenter (''screenshot big''), a big screenshot will be made.
* '''script [<file>]''' -- ''Record a script to the file named <file>''
* '''scrollto <tile>''' -- ''Scroll to the tile numbered <tile>; hexadecimal (prexifed with 0x) and decimal values supported''
* '''set <setting> <value>''' -- ''Set <setting> to <value>''
** This command can be used to set various game-related options. The following options are known:
*** ''autoclean_companies on/off'' -- Enable this to declare empty companies (companies with no activate clients) bankrupt after a certain amount of months (see below)
*** ''autoclean_protected <months>'' -- Delay in in-game months before a protected company is declared bankrupt
*** ''autoclean_unprotected <months>'' -- Delay in in-game month before an unprotected company is declared bankrupt
*** ''company_pw "<password>"'' -- Sets the password of the current players company. Set the password to * to disable it.
*** ''name "<playername>"'' -- Sets the current players name
*** ''server_name "<name>"'' -- Sets the servers name
*** ''server_advertise on/off'' -- Enable this to report your server to the master server. This controls whether your server is visible in the internet server list or not
*** ''server_bind_ip <ip>'' -- Binds the server to a specific IP. Standard setting is 0.0.0.0 so the server binds itself to all available IPs of the computer
*** ''server_port <port>'' -- Sets the port where the server listens for connections.
*** ''server_pw "<password>"'' -- Sets the password which is needed to join the server. Set the password to * to disable it.
*** ''restart_game_date "<year>"'' -- Sets the year when the game ends and a new one starts
*** ''patch <patch_name> [<value>]'' -- Changes the value of a patch or reads its value out.
* '''status''' -- ''Get status information on all currently connected clients''
* '''unban <ip> <warning>(r1620)</warning>''' -- ''Remove given IP out of the ban list.''


